rfetch is a ruby gem to manage remote-project-sets (rps) for different repositories

usage: rfetch [-f <rps-file>|{rfetch.rps}] [-d <directory>|{.}] <command>

were command is

-pull			pull remote to local
-push			push local to remote
-revert			revert local
-tag <url>		tag local to url

were rps is a file of format:

<rps nature="rps-nature(SVN|GIT|...)">
	<container uri="container-uri">
		<entry name="entry-name" [loc="local-name"|{name}] [rev="revision"|{HEAD}] />
		...
	</container>
	...
</rps>